        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer878887530" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12226766985610354456">Hello my Goodreads fam👋🏽. I just completed 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐝𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐖𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫 for the 2nd time. And mannnnn, I forgot how freakin awesome this book is! That ending just blew me away😯. <br/><br/>I feel like I need to go back and reread 𝐌𝐢𝐝𝐧𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 now. To be honest I stopped reading the Midnight Trilogy after the first book because I didn’t like the direction Sister Souljah took with Midnight’s love interest. Maybe after reading 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞 𝐀𝐟𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐡 I’ll give 𝐀 𝐌𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐎𝐟 𝐒𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 and 𝐌𝐢𝐝𝐧𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐌𝐞𝐚𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐨𝐟 𝐋𝐨𝐯𝐞 a try. <br/><br/>I</span>
  <span id="freeText12226766985610354456" style="display:none">Hello my Goodreads fam👋🏽. I just completed 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐂𝐨𝐥𝐝𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐖𝐢𝐧𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐄𝐯𝐞𝐫 for the 2nd time. And mannnnn, I forgot how freakin awesome this book is! That ending just blew me away😯. <br /><br />I feel like I need to go back and reread 𝐌𝐢𝐝𝐧𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 now. To be honest I stopped reading the Midnight Trilogy after the first book because I didn’t like the direction Sister Souljah took with Midnight’s love interest. Maybe after reading 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞 𝐀𝐟𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐡 I’ll give 𝐀 𝐌𝐨𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭 𝐎𝐟 𝐒𝐢𝐥𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞 and 𝐌𝐢𝐝𝐧𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐌𝐞𝐚𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐨𝐟 𝐋𝐨𝐯𝐞 a try. <br /><br />I never read 𝐀 𝐃𝐞𝐞𝐩𝐞𝐫 𝐋𝐨𝐯𝐞 𝐈𝐧𝐬𝐢𝐝𝐞: 𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐏𝐨𝐫𝐬𝐜𝐡𝐞 𝐒𝐚𝐧𝐭𝐢𝐚𝐠𝐚 𝐒𝐭𝐨𝐫𝐲. But after that last chapter of CWE I feel like I have to read it. I’m sure Porsche is colder than Winter. <br /><br />But for now I’m going right into the sequel 𝐋𝐢𝐟𝐞 𝐀𝐟𝐭𝐞𝐫 𝐃𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐡. I’m really enjoy this journey.</span>
