<div id="review_1011851587" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1011851587" />
    <a title="Tyla Rodriguez" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21131995-tyla-rodriguez"><img alt="Tyla Rodriguez" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1404058408p2/21131995.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1011851587?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tyla Rodriguez" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tyla Rodriguez" href="/user/show/21131995-tyla-rodriguez">Tyla Rodriguez</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9781416521693" href="/book/show/106393.The_Coldest_Winter_Ever">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1011851587" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16458666269351343219">One word: OVERRATED. I expected something with twists and a great plot. At least for the character to learn something from all that she went through, and believe me, it was a bunch of dumb, unnecessary BS. Almost as if the author just needed filler material for her &quot;novel&quot;. The writing was weak and don&apos;t even get me started on the grammatical errors. <br/><br/>Winter Santiaga, the books protagonist, is EXTREMELY unlikable. She&apos;s materialistic and self consumed. To really get into a book, I have to like th</span>
  <span id="freeText16458666269351343219" style="display:none">One word: OVERRATED. I expected something with twists and a great plot. At least for the character to learn something from all that she went through, and believe me, it was a bunch of dumb, unnecessary BS. Almost as if the author just needed filler material for her "novel". The writing was weak and don't even get me started on the grammatical errors. <br /><br />Winter Santiaga, the books protagonist, is EXTREMELY unlikable. She's materialistic and self consumed. To really get into a book, I have to like the characters or feel pity for them. I didn't like anyone from this book, which made it hard to push through. I didn't even like Sister Souljah and found her character to be really pointless because she did not contribute anything to the story. It's not like Winter learned anything from her, which is what you would expect. She was just another part of the book that could have easily been excluded. In a word, this book was terrible. Terrible writing, character development, dialogue, just terrible. I'm just glad to be done with it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16458666269351343219" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


