<div id="review_17216304" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/17216304" />
    <a title="Kellee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/966794-kellee"><img alt="Kellee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1379209625p2/966794.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/17216304?book_show_action=true">Mar 06, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kellee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kellee" href="/user/show/966794-kellee">Kellee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9781416521693" href="/book/show/106393.The_Coldest_Winter_Ever">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer17216304" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8347500695831686439">I read this book at least 3 times. This used to be my favorite book. I first read it in high school and loved it. I then read it a few years after that and again after that. Each time it was good, but the original excitement was taken away. If you haven&apos;t read it, buy a cop and read it because it&apos;s worth it. I just think I read it too many times.</span>
  <span id="freeText8347500695831686439" style="display:none">I read this book at least 3 times. This used to be my favorite book. I first read it in high school and loved it. I then read it a few years after that and again after that. Each time it was good, but the original excitement was taken away. If you haven't read it, buy a cop and read it because it's worth it. I just think I read it too many times.</span>
